To ensure effective operations in support of the Country Programme, UNICEF shifted Master Data Management to BTC/Finance with extensive data cleaning, strengthened internal and external complaint management and risk assessment, and built new procurement partnerships.

UNICEF and partners have achieved important results in improving immunization and health services, conducting a first health system evaluation and the effective implementation of the prevention of mother-to-child HIV transmission.

The policy environment for youth-inclusive, participatory policy-making improved with multisectoral governmental roadmap Words of Youth; aiming at promoting youth empowerment and entrepreneurship. Capacity for budget data transparency, long-term scenarios building and prospective planning and the shift to outcome-oriented budget programs help increase accountability, efficiency and equity of government's budget.
